captions.text: - [Tyler] So much happened in 2014.
I recapped 2013.

PBS did a documentary about
me called Generation Like.

I told you whether or not
size actually matters.
Hosted a Grammy live stream.
Taught you all about Shanghai and Dubai.
Hosted Fifth Harmony's Barbie launch.

Set some ground rules
for our little fandom.

Did a collaboration with
DoSomething.org's puppet sloth.
Attended the Super Bowl with Pepsi.
Explored San Francisco.
Was a guest on Grace Helbig's podcast.

Told you about the time
I lost my virginity.

Celebrated Valentine's Day
with The Boyfriend Tag.

Played What is in My
Mouth with Ricky Dillon.
Toured in Hawaii with O2L.
Had a meeting with President Barack Obama.
Celebrated St. Patrick's Day with Sawyer.
Joined the Real Housewives.
Was on a South by Southwest panel.

Guest starred in The Most
Popular Girls in School.
Attended Play List Live.
Turned 25 years old.
Reacted to my own birth with my mom.

Had a photo shoot spread
featured in Tiger Beat Magazine.
Worked the MTV Movie Awards red carpet.
Taught y'all how to make sure that
fame does not go to your head.
Raised half a million dollars for
suicide prevention for my birthday.
Was a guest on The Insider.

Attempted The Chicken
Nugget Challenge again.
Made a new, updated vision board.

Was told by Ellen Degeneres
that she was a fan.
Won Most Valuable Slayer.
Interviewed celebrities on the
Kid's Choice Awards red carpet.
Created a YouTuber burn book.
Attended ITAtube in Italy.

Went on an Italian road
trip with the YouTube boys.
Hosted The Fault in Our Stars
soundtrack concert live stream.
Did The Humming Challenge with Betty Who.

Attended YouTube Fan Fest
in Singapore and Sydney.
Got silly in Perth, Australia.
Taught y'all The Best Friend Booger Test.
Through teaming up with my people

became the Trevor Project's
largest individual

donor and was awarded the
Trevor Youth Innovator award.
Was a guest on Joan Rivers' web series,
In Bed with Joan.
Absolutely slayed VidCon.
Got my face burned off by Tanya Burr.
Attempted to play the Kim Kardashian game.
Hosted the MTV Fandom Awards.
Was nominated for a Young Hollywood Award.
Launched my second annual Auguest month.

Played The Seven Seconds
Challenge with Tanya.

Created The Poopy Diaper
Challenge with Korey.
Morphed YouTubers with Marcus.
Ate weiners with SuperFruit.
Performed a Q and Slay with Queen Jackie.
Had a drunk puppet show with Mamrie.

Did The Photo Booth
Challenge with Miranda.

Did The Drunk Backwards
Words Challenge with Sawyer.
Waxed my legs with Jenna Marbles.
Played Fuck, Marry, Kill with Jim.

Whispered some awkward
pick up lines with Connor.
Tie dyed a bunch of clothes with Hannah.
Electrocuted myself with Joe Sugg.
Exposed YouTuber rumors with Caspar.
Guessed some first tweets with Alfie.
Watched disturbing porn with Dan.
Played Things with Grace.
Made pottery with Troye.
Had a Disney Challenge rematch with Zoe.
Got intimate with my boy Darren Criss.
Attended Summer in the City in London.
Debuted my new podcast Psychobabble
number one on the charts.

Announced my very own
Solo Slumber Party tour.

Won two Teen Choice
Awards thanks to you guys.
Interviewed celebrities at the MTV VMA's.

Hosted an Emmy's viewing
party live stream.

Became a Taco Bell Foundation
for Teens ambassador.
Participated in Al Gore's
24 Hours of Climate Reality special.

Was honored as the Streamys
Activist Icon of the Year.

Won Entertainer of the
Year at the Streamy Awards.

Made a little collaboration
with Michelle Obama.

Had a photo shoot spread
in Seventeen Magazine.

Honored Google and YouTube with
an award at the GLAAD GALA.
Taught y'all not accept pickle juice.
Went to Zoe's product launch in London.
Was a guest on The Talk.

Collaborated with the
one and only Julie Chen.
Had my very own BBC One radio special.

Did a christmassy photo
shoot for Paper Magazine.
Became a professional hula hooper.
Won the Out100 Readers' Choice Award.
Gave my bedroom a makeover.

Was Finn the Human from
Adventure Time for Halloween.
Presented at the NewNowNext Awards.

Crashed a homecoming with
Charli XCX and Bella Thorne.
Made some papier-mache heads with Korey.

Twerked with Jessie J to be
a part of Just Dance 2015.

Co-hosted The Trevor
Live Gala's red carpet.
Reacted to teens reacting to me.

Sent y'all a very sloppy
Christmas message.
Celebrated my seventh year on YouTube
by reaching six million subscribers.

Served you some Katy
Perry circa Dark Horse
in YouTube Rewind 2014.

And rang in the new year
in Sydney, Australia.
So I guess it was kind of a good year.
If you've been with me for a while now
thank you so much for being a part
of my year and I cannot wait to take you
on more adventures in 2015.
If you're new here be sure to subscribe
for new videos every single week.
Bye y'all.
(upbeat music)

comments.text:
Hello there, Tyler.

I have been on the internet since I was 7. I started watching YouTube in 
late 2007 when I was 12. I have watched hundreds of thousands of videos 
(not including rewatches). I used to watch around 8 hours of YouTube a day 
in high school. Out of all the content that I have been exposed to on the 
internet, I can honestly say that you are one of the most inspirational 
creators out there. You don't sit behind a mask or a character in order to 
fit into society or what society says or expects you should be. You have an 
amazing personality that has a perfect blend of empathy and confidence 
without being gullible or prideful. You are not afraid to stand out from 
the crowd. You go out of your way to let people, complete strangers at 
that, realize that they are not alone. You make them laugh, think, and 
relate to not only you, but everyone else that watches you. Your level of 
ambition is absolutely astounding, and just the aura that it gives off can 
inspire so many people to be better and to work harder. I feel that someone 
could get to know you like friend simply by watching your videos. This is 
extremely rare nowadays, and I never stumble upon people so true to 
themselves anymore.

That's enough ass kissing for one paragraph. 

I should stop being so impersonal and explain who I am. My name is Dylan. I 
am 20 years old, and I live in New Orleans, Louisiana, USA. I have been 
through a lot of things through my life that have shaped me into who I am. 
From being bullied, to living with split custody at a very young age, I 
have been through some shit. Something that I feel has shaped me the most, 
however, is a condition that I was diagnosed with since I was six. I have 
ADHD.

This brings me to why I decided to write this comment.

As someone with ADHD, I can tell you that it is difficult to motivate me to 
do something that I do not want to do. I like to call ADHD the "give a 
fuck" condition because it is really easy to tell if you care at all about 
what is being presented to you. If you don't care, you simply cannot pay 
attention to it. If you do care, you can't find enough time in the day to 
be interested in it.

This was highly apparent in my high school years when I could not focus on 
important classes. It came to a point when I was so helpless to my 
condition that I couldn't get my grades to go up no matter how hard I 
tried. I fell into depression from the sheer pressure to succeed. I stopped 
talking to my parents and hanging out with my friends. I became extremely 
anxious and would spend hours in my room staring at a wall, wondering how 
miserable my life would be without a good education. I attempted suicide a 
few times, but thankfully never went through with it. 

The last time I tried to off myself was when I realized why I was 
miserable. I was so focused on making other people happy with my 
accomplishments that I never considered my own happiness into the equation. 
I realized that nobody could help me fix this problem. I had to fix this 
problem alone. I decided to stop caring so much about impressing everyone 
else and started to try to impress myself. From that day on, I would strive 
to do better than I thought I was capable of, no matter what the subject 
may be. THAT would be my motivation.

I am now the first in my family on both sides to get into college, 
somewhere no one thought I would get to. Somewhere *I* never thought I 
would get to. Somewhere they *told* me I would never get to.

Sometimes you just have to find the right motivation to bring out a drive 
that you didn't know you had. It took me a bit longer than most people, but 
I eventually found it through the darkness and the pain. I never want 
anyone around me to have to find motivation like that, and that is why I 
love your videos.

You have accomplished so much in your life, Tyler. You have used your power 
to inspire most, if not all of your fans to be better simply by being you. 
They don't have to go through the hell that I did to find a drive. You have 
helped people in ways that you can't even imagine.

Keep on slaying, Tyler.﻿
